<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
Sinistar2 wrote:<BR>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Sword of Xuzl - Give me a way to boost the damage of my Sword of Xuzl (Augment only improves the speed, hitpoints, and armor class of the sword but not the amount of damage it does/second.&nbsp; Armor class and hitpoints are worthless when the sword only has about 100 hitpoints to begin with.&nbsp; Usually 1 hit in the planes of power knocks it out.&nbsp; How about letting the sword crit at my regular crit rate (which is 18% thank you very much and will go to 20% tonight when I hit 65).</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Content - Cobalt Scar was once called the Druid and Wizard's private hunting preserve because we had the only way to get there.&nbsp; How about some more zones where other groups need a porter to get there.&nbsp; You don't have to make those zones Quadding heaven but make them desirable for other classes so they want a Wizard or Druid to take them there.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>These are just a few suggestions to help our class.&nbsp; Small advanced on any of these fronts would be greatly appreciated.&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Best Regards,</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Sinistar2</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV><BR>
<HR>
</BLOCKQUOTE><BR>
<DIV>But, but, but... they gave us Solist's Frozen Sword...</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Allow me to point out that a wizard/druid only accesible zone would do 2 things only:&nbsp;Increase the amount of port requests (decent if you like the cash flow from ports), and increase the level of whining from port defficient (as well as some members of the porting community) due to the difficulty of getting there.&nbsp; I'd like to further point out that WoS and beyond were&nbsp;just a touch less difficult&nbsp;to access by non-porters as Cobalt Scar was (cobalt scar only having issues due to the need for the key)</DIV>	
