<P>I wouldn't be suggesting any abilities that arn't going to help a wizard, stuns and roots arn't even imminent domain of a wizard, have the abilities but in our hands are typically weak tools, (stuns create too much agro for a class that is already agro-burden, not too mention less and less of content is even stunnable,&nbsp; In general people don't like root, it's unreliable it leaves an open mob, and a wizard has no means of moving the mob outta of the way, either thru non-dmg agro (ranger/druid snares)&nbsp;and/or non-dmg movement spells (ie pally stuns)&nbsp; Whereas nuking multiple mobs at once surely should be a wizard's delight, it's outside the scope of this game minus very few instances.&nbsp; The matter of fact is people do not want to fight 1.5k hitters times 2 at once, and quite honestly I don't want to be on agro of 2 1.5k mobs at the same time myself~</P>	
