	<tr>
	
		<td class="msg_user_cell" width="150" valign=top>
		
			 









<a href='/eq/view_profile?user.id=103825'  class="auth_text"  style="font-weight:bold;" >	
Aramel</a>
			<br>
			
			<span style="font-size: 8pt;">
			Newbie<br>
			
				Posts: 4<br>
				
				Registered: 05-15-2005
				
			</span>
			


			
			<br>
			
				<img src="/i/p.gif" height=8 width=150 border=0 alt=""><br>
				
			<a href='/eq/view_profile?user.id=103825'>







<img src="/eq/i/icons/Classes/wizard.gif" border=0 alt=""/></a><br>
			


			
			<p>
			






<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=wizardbalance&message.id=4179#M4179">36</a> of 38
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 194 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV>
<DIV>The fact that wizards generally deal 1/3 and under of a rogue's dps and that even rangers are starting to deal more damage has by now (as mentioned by many already) made our class obsolete.&nbsp; Getting invited to groups merely because I can snare and no druids/ranges/sk/necros are lfg is just a minor example of how sad the situation is, not to mention the waste of space we now are to a raiding guild.&nbsp; Wizards should without question deal more damage than any other class in the game while they still have mana (and for longer than 90 sec...), that is the reason we exist in the first place.&nbsp; Understandeably rogues should then have a greater sustained dps, but only by a slight margin.&nbsp; To make things fair this could be the same margin by which wizards out dps them in burst damage.&nbsp; To equalize this problem is not as difficult as has been suggested, and I do not imply we should be overpowered either.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>1) Create a wizard only aa that makes our spells less resistable.&nbsp; No other class suffers from resists to the degree that we do.&nbsp; Mages have their pets and related aas, and an amazing DS that they can chain cast on the MT for 0 aggro.&nbsp; The same is true for Necros, and while they may get a few DoT resists, after recasting them a couple of times it will last the entire fight.&nbsp; Enchanters, well, all they need to do is debuff the mob&nbsp;a couple of times per fight and are supposed to have poor dps.&nbsp; Druids act more as healers on raids anyways, and group mobs dont resist to a level that their own debuffs cannot acount for.&nbsp; Yes I love our epic effect, but even that is not nerely effective enough (and naturally hard to attain for many wizards).&nbsp; Melee get strikethrough, is that not the same as reducing an npc's resists?&nbsp; For those special ultra resisting encounters, improove the efficiency of our Lure spells, including Meteor Storm and its fulture upgrades (which I thought was a great addition in principle).</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>2) Improve Critical blasts.&nbsp; I am happy that only wizards recieved a crit aa in dodh, but the improoved dps from crits is nowhere near that of melee.&nbsp; After spending an absurd amount of aa, the frequency of critical blasts is disproportionately low.&nbsp; Improving this is an easy way for our aggro issues to be partially solved.&nbsp; Fix frenzied devastation, melee classes have countless aas/ailities that improove dps without severely hampering their ability to deal damage once its finished.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>3) Focus items/familiars.&nbsp; Melee get proc rate improvements and similar&nbsp;modifications to skills/equipment equivalent to our focus items.&nbsp; The random nature of focuses undermines their utility.&nbsp; If you can, raise the probability that a 50% focus item will actually improove spell damage by 50% not by an average of 30.&nbsp; If not give us an aa which does this, or raises the minimum cap by a proportion.&nbsp; Yes finally make our familiars stackeable with bard song, for bard haste (and other melee songs) most definately stack with every discipline melees have.&nbsp; A great idea would to be to introduce 'the ultimate flappy', wich would require all 3&nbsp;Greater familiars aswell as devoted, and combine the stats of Devoted with a 35% focus to cold,fire and magic, with perhaps a modest&nbsp;increase to resists.&nbsp; As a tangent you can even revive more spells like Ice Flame of Eci.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>4) Spell haste.&nbsp; If you disaprove of our getting larger DD spells, then help us cast faster, which directly increases our dps.&nbsp; This can be done either through more aa, modifying existing spells or even a new line which similarly to mana weave, procs spell haste (making the next spell instant for example).&nbsp; Another idea is to have an aa which operates in the same way as pyromancy,&nbsp;giving a % of aggro reduction, (that increases per rank etc) which costs an amout of mana/tick to keep active.&nbsp; Since ice is the 'efficient' line this could be Hydromancy, that would thus not stack with pyro.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>5) Assorted damage abilities.&nbsp; I must say I was extremely pleased with virtually everything wizards got in the last expansion.&nbsp; The ability to deal 20k damage for 1 mana really makes me feel we are starting to move in the right direction (and of course the effect of mana weave which allows for such damage).&nbsp; But being able to do this, while satisfying, only happens extremely rarely.&nbsp; Pyromancy is very nice, and in my opinion needs no changes to it.&nbsp; Our Call of Xuzil (average of 3.5-4k damage) and sword pets (about the same in a 4 min fight) are also nice aditions and should not be changed either, but are again&nbsp;by no means significant dps (really they exist for the push factor).&nbsp; For our ward of destruction I also agree with Kristie, it should do something useful to the group, raising the damage base of spells, with possibly a mana regen component, or just remain the same but ONLY damage unmezzed npcs.&nbsp; Finally there is Manaburn.&nbsp; A large topic in itself, but I have little to say on it myself except that the proposed changes seem acceptable, and that I really do not want a 'better' manaburn to replace improvements in our conventional damage.&nbsp;&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>6) An&nbsp;"evade' type&nbsp;spell.&nbsp; This is the big addition that should finally solve our aggro problems.&nbsp; If all my other suggestions are less practical this is the sole one that "must" be implemented.&nbsp; Rogues get evade itlsef, monks, sk&nbsp;and necromancers have FD, Berzerkers I'm not sure what they have but manage to dish out insane dps unscathed,&nbsp;while every other class is not pure dps and so&nbsp;has no significant (or unjustifiable) issues with aggro.&nbsp; It would be no exploitation and make perfect sense, the wizard uses his knowledge of translocation to briefly shift out of the material plane, making the mob forget him (a guaranteed move down the hate list).&nbsp; In theory with our current spells/aa etc we can roughly&nbsp;do a near indefinite&nbsp; 400 dps (CoV), an average of 750-800 (Core Fire) and a maximum of 1k+ (Ether Flame), but if we actually did that much on a real mob, we would gain aggro (using Ele pants, MC, and SC, and with epic 2, and even with an enc spamming visage!!) before even being half way into a fight.&nbsp; Not only do&nbsp;rogues inherently generate less aggro (which I suppose we can accept) while doing 900-1.3k+, when they eventually do, all they need is to press a button and its gone.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>7) More spell casting subtlety aas.&nbsp; I suppose an ancient concussion clicky would be nice, but&nbsp;more aas is probably a preferable solution.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>8) Mass Teleportation.&nbsp; We now have knowledge stones, Wayfarer Magus, Translocators across Norrath, and a guild hall portal.&nbsp; So why can we still not translocate our raids to specific location?&nbsp; Is Maelin slacking again?&nbsp; Yes we can mass TL to guild hall and my own guild has that arangement, but&nbsp;it is no great effort to create&nbsp;'translocate group' versions of our group gates, and then make us pay 9 aa to have mgb.&nbsp; After all, necros get mgb just so they can give their raid dmf.&nbsp; Of course this is at the very bottom of our list of fixes, but a good proposition none the less.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>9) Forget Utility.&nbsp; This is important, I noticed that&nbsp;in the last patch a level 70 DD with a 5 tick mezz component was introduced to the live servers (though players cannot use it as yet).&nbsp; We are not enchanters, and we don't want to become the bard of&nbsp;casters either.&nbsp; If you want to give us this spell anyways then I&nbsp;find it a great idea and welcome it, but the last thing I want is for this, and other&nbsp;'utility' additions&nbsp;to be treated&nbsp;as a compromise for not solving our fundamental problems.&nbsp; Rogues do two things; dps and cr.&nbsp; Likewise all we should do is dps and gate (which is not to say that our forms of dps should not be creative and varied!!).&nbsp; Damage is the most useful thing a wizard can provide and is in itself equally important as the main strengths of other classes that focus on buffing/healing/croud control etc...</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>10) Caster Item effects.&nbsp; Melee get; strikethrough, weapon procs, combat effects,&nbsp; more attack and haste from items as well as wepon bonuses +% to backstab, bash, (that equates I guess with +% evocation for example)&nbsp;lower discipline use time&nbsp;etc... all of which stack up to a relatively high cap that can be raised in some cases with aas.&nbsp; We on the other hand get...mana.&nbsp; Focus effects account for some of this, but are nowhere close to the dps improvements melee can get through equipment (especially due to the random nature mentioned above) and naturally do not stack.&nbsp; Perhaps I exagerate, but it seems to me that equipment is starting to get very melee intensive.&nbsp; From their perspective I imagine it is true in a way that all we need to do is get a spell and an apropriate focus item to attain our maximum dps potential (obviously we need mana to feed it, but thats not the point), and perhaps this is the reason why we are not getting the kind of spells we need, since melee classes have to collect all this gear in order to reach their max potential.&nbsp; If this is the case, why&nbsp;not give casters&nbsp;item effects, +10&nbsp;to fire spells for instance, or a variety of options that the development team can come up with (available to all casters of course).&nbsp; This can include improvements to our mana regen, and means to raise our caps (it is absurd that we already reach the present cap with just clairvoyance and our familiar, and not benefit from mana increasing items.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>What I have proposed are realistic and reasonable improvements to the wizard class.&nbsp; If there are still some concerns that making us decent dps in raids will overpower us in groups situations (which I fail to see personally), bane spells can be introduced which only affect raid targets.&nbsp; New code could also be created to prevent KSing with caps and such if that is another concern (though as a non-programer I have no idea how hard this may be so please excuse me in advance).&nbsp; We don't want to be able to kill things with one or two spells (well I would, but in all fairness would never seriously suggest that <img src='/i/smilies/16x16_smiley-tongue.gif' width=16 height=16 border=0>), we just want a reason to continue to play this game.&nbsp; I think I speak for many wizards when I say that I am tired of pretending&nbsp;to be&nbsp;decent dps. &nbsp;It is simply not fair, and something significant needs to be done.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Aramelnir Sapientia</DIV></DIV>	
		</td></tr>
		<tr>
		
