<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=wizardbalance&message.id=4667#M4667">38</a> of 38
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 54 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		
				background-color: #050A0E; 
				
				 background-image: none;
				 
				background-repeat: repeat-x;
				" 
			>
			<DIV></DIV>
<DIV>Aggro/Hate per cast, damage to mana ratio, resist rates,&nbsp;and maybe even melee damage mitigation can all <STRONG>easily be fixed</STRONG> by adding to the existing line of Familiars&nbsp;the Wizard class already has.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><U>Changes such as:</U></DIV>
<P>Increase the amount of mana&nbsp;to the existing familiar line.</P>
<P>Increase the mana regen per tick modifier to the existing familiar line.</P>
<P>Increase the damage percentage modifier to the existing damage increasing familiar line (substantially).</P>
<P>Add a negative percentage to aggro on the familiar line. If it can be added to an item, it can be added to Familiars.</P>
<P>Add a resist decreasing component to the familiar line. If it can be added to an item, it can be added to Familiars.</P>
<P>Add an over-the-item-cap avoidance percentage to the existing familiar line.</P>
<P><EM>Combinations of the above are&nbsp;important, we need more than one tweak!</EM></P>
<DIV><STRONG>In my opinion</STRONG>, the introduction of the Familiar line was the first attempt to "fix" the Wizard in the first place. Do it again with the above type ideas. Don't use raw numbers please!! Use percentages, such that their usefulness will scale up and down the level range and not be rendered ineffective by each new expansion.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>There is&nbsp;very little&nbsp;limitation to what could be added to the existing Familiar line of buffs to enhance the Wizard in such a way that would be very easy to test, adjust, or implement in both the coding and test server environment. Even an AA or set of AAs that enhanced the Familiar in the above ways would work great and still be easy as well.</DIV>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
							Faelin Crimsoncloud<br>Rodcet Nife<br>Brew Masters
							</div>
								
		</td></tr>
